You can please everyone (porn lovers and people who don't want to see NSFW stuff) by structuring your video site using hubs. You don't have to host pornhub (haha get it?) but you can open the possibility for another user to host it, and people who want to see it can download it, while those who don't want to see it can exercise self restraint and not download it.
This will allow people to publish videos that are illegal or violate your sense of morality. But you won't have to seed, support, or partake in that.
This way will result in less bickering about the use of tags as well, since people will presumably upload videos onto a suitable hub.
if each user its their own hub, wouldn't it become very difficult to find videos to watch if you don't have each of those hubs already downloaded?
Maybe users can be their own hubs, but in addition to that there could be large topic-focused public hubs they can contribute to as well?
I don't think it would create any additional burden to develop or maintain, since a public hub is just a "user" hub/channel with a rule allowing "*" to sign and publish.
